01:08:48.428 --> 01:08:51.470
So jump fast to save yourself.

817
01:08:51.970 --> 01:08:53.594
OK...

818
01:08:54.261 --> 01:08:57.428
Oh. and there's a branch sticking out
about halfway down. so jump out.

819
01:08:58.802 --> 01:09:00.345
You're really selling this.

820
01:09:02.970 --> 01:09:04.552
Is that poison ivy?

821
01:09:08.970 --> 01:09:10.595
Holy shit!

822
01:09:11.886 --> 01:09:12.928
OK...

823
01:09:15.011 --> 01:09:16.387
Should we leave a note

824
01:09:16.470 --> 01:09:18.470
in case people think it's a joint suicide?

825
01:09:19.095 --> 01:09:20.718
Nah. let's keep 'em guessing.

826
01:09:24.886 --> 01:09:27.553
Yeah. there's the shaky legs.

827
01:09:30.637 --> 01:09:31.928
OK.

828
01:09:32.387 --> 01:09:34.303
One. two...

829
01:09:34.387 --> 01:09:35.719
Wait. wait. wait. wait. wait!

830
01:09:36.470 --> 01:09:37.718
Three! Saving myself!

831
01:09:41.095 --> 01:09:42.761
No! Whoo!

832
01:09:45.511 --> 01:09:47.345
Yeah! That hurt.

833
01:09:56.262 --> 01:09:58.011
Fishing vessel Angela Rose.

834
01:09:58.095 --> 01:10:00.095
Fishing vessel Angela Rose. Coast guard.

835
01:10:00.178 --> 01:10:02.719
25 off your starboard quarter.
Channel 16. over.

836
01:10:05.220 --> 01:10:07.719
Fishing vessel Angela Rose.
Fishing vessel Angela Rose.

837
01:10:07.803 --> 01:10:10.637
Coast guard. 25. E21. 25. E21.

838
01:10:10.719 --> 01:10:13.345
Channel 16. Come in. Over.

839
01:10:20.303 --> 01:10:22.679
Fishing vessel Angela Rose.
Fishing vessel Angela Rose.

840
01:10:22.761 --> 01:10:25.761
Coast guard. 25. E21. 25. E21.

841
01:10:25.844 --> 01:10:27.719
Come in. Over.

842
01:10:29.844 --> 01:10:32.719
Fishing vessel Angela Rose.
Fishing vessel Angela Rose.

843
01:10:32.803 --> 01:10:35.095
Coast guard 25. You are in violation of...

844
01:10:43.178 --> 01:10:44.345
You. sir! Sir. stand up!

845
01:10:44.428 --> 01:10:47.178
Drop the pick. Stand up!
Stand up! What's going on here?

846
01:10:47.262 --> 01:10:49.595
Why is no one answering the radio?

847
01:11:14.262 --> 01:11:15.262
Nailed it.

848
01:11:17.512 --> 01:11:18.637
No!

849
01:11:20.845 --> 01:11:22.428
- No!
- No. no!

850
01:11:24.803 --> 01:11:26.178
Check it out!

851
01:11:28.928 --> 01:11:30.053
Yeah. yeah. yeah!

852
01:11:40.886 --> 01:11:42.178
Yeah! No!

853
01:12:33.303 --> 01:12:34.303
What happened?

854
01:12:35.761 --> 01:12:37.886
You didn't come to work.

855
01:12:37.970 --> 01:12:39.803
We're done fishing.

856
01:12:39.886 --> 01:12:41.719
They suspended my license.

857
01:12:42.803 --> 01:12:43.970
Who?

858
01:12:44.761 --> 01:12:45.761
Coasties.

859
01:12:45.845 --> 01:12:48.970
The observer saw we were deaf
and tipped them off.

860
01:12:49.387 --> 01:12:51.262
Well. they can't do that.

861
01:12:51.345 --> 01:12:53.137
We were just working

862
01:12:53.220 --> 01:12:56.137
and they came to board us. We didn't know.

863
01:12:56.220 --> 01:12:57.345
I told you.

864
01:12:57.429 --> 01:12:58.637
You need a hearing deckhand.

865
01:12:59.845 --> 01:13:01.303
Yeah. that's you!

866
01:13:01.387 --> 01:13:02.429
You were that person!

867
01:13:02.512 --> 01:13:04.720
I can't always be that person!

868
01:13:05.178 --> 01:13:07.053
She's right. We need another guy.

869
01:13:07.137 --> 01:13:08.303
We can't afford it!

870
01:13:10.512 --> 01:13:13.512
If you'd told me you weren't coming.

871
01:13:13.595 --> 01:13:15.970
I'd have figured something out.
But you didn't.

872
01:13:16.679 --> 01:13:18.595
You're seriously blaming me?

873
01:13:19.429 --> 01:13:21.429
Your father was counting on you.

874
01:13:25.512 --> 01:13:28.303
No. Don't put this on me.

875
01:13:30.637 --> 01:13:32.720
It's not my fault.

876
01:13:39.554 --> 01:13:42.761
You failed to obey an order
by federal law enforcement

877
01:13:42.845 --> 01:13:44.512
to board your vessel.

878
01:13:45.095 --> 01:13:48.053
On top of that.
you were operating your vessel

879
01:13:48.137 --> 01:13:50.845
in a negligent and dangerous manner

880
01:13:50.928 --> 01:13:53.637
due to your... disability.

881
01:13:55.137 --> 01:14:00.345
I have no choice but to administer
the minimum fine. which is $1.000.

882
01:14:00.803 --> 01:14:04.928
and an additional penalty of $1.500.

883
01:14:09.845 --> 01:14:14.429
We can't pay that unless
we can get back on the water.

884
01:14:15.095 --> 01:14:17.637
Officer. what do they need
to do to be able to fish again?

885
01:14:18.928 --> 01:14:22.429
You will be required
to have a hearing individual

886
01:14:22.512 --> 01:14:25.012
on board at all times

887
01:14:25.095 --> 01:14:28.928
to answer radios.
hear ship whistles. etcetera.

888
01:14:29.637 --> 01:14:33.637
We will be monitoring you regularly
to make sure you are in compliance.

889
01:14:34.720 --> 01:14:36.595
Do you have that person?

890
01:14:58.886 --> 01:15:01.137
I'll sell the boat.

891
01:15:01.220 --> 01:15:05.304
Take the money we can. That'll be that.

892
01:15:06.262 --> 01:15:07.512
It's fine.

893
01:15:08.178 --> 01:15:09.637
I'll stay.

894
01:15:10.803 --> 01:15:12.970
I'll work with you on the boat.

895
01:15:13.053 --> 01:15:14.596
No!

896
01:15:14.679 --> 01:15:15.761
Yes.

897
01:15:15.845 --> 01:15:17.886
We can't afford to pay someone else.

898
01:15:19.970 --> 01:15:22.886
And there's nobody that's
gonna know how to sign.

899
01:15:24.554 --> 01:15:25.886
Are you sure?

900
01:15:26.554 --> 01:15:28.262
School can wait.

901
01:15:30.304 --> 01:15:32.262
I already decided.

902
01:15:33.679 --> 01:15:35.137
I'm excited.

903
01:15:40.012 --> 01:15:42.137
Oh. Saint Ruby!

904
01:15:42.220 --> 01:15:44.429
We'll make a shrine to you on the boat.

905
01:15:44.512 --> 01:15:45.512
Wait!

906
01:15:45.554 --> 01:15:46.554
She's trying to help!

907
01:15:47.053 --> 01:15:48.720
Well. thank God you have her.

908
01:16:13.928 --> 01:16:15.845
Don't kill me.

909
01:16:17.596 --> 01:16:23.512
I bought you a red dress for your concert.

910
01:16:29.179 --> 01:16:31.845
If you don't like it.
you don't have to wear it.

911
01:16:36.637 --> 01:16:39.387
I'm really glad you're staying.

912
01:16:42.220 --> 01:16:43.637
Leo isn't.

913
01:16:44.637 --> 01:16:45.970
It's complicated.

914
01:16:46.345 --> 01:16:47.679
He feels...

915
01:16:48.387 --> 01:16:49.512
left out.

916
01:16:50.554 --> 01:16:51.887
That's crazy.

917
01:16:53.220 --> 01:16:55.637
It's always the three of you

918
01:16:55.720 --> 01:16:56.928
and then me.

919
01:17:00.429 --> 01:17:02.053
I get it.

920
01:17:11.970 --> 01:17:15.679
Do you ever wish I was deaf?

921
01:17:28.970 --> 01:17:32.512
When you were born. at the hospital.

922
01:17:33.720 --> 01:17:36.387
they gave you a hearing test.

923
01:17:38.012 --> 01:17:42.345
And there you were. so tiny and sweet.

924
01:17:44.262 --> 01:17:47.137
with these electrodes all over you.

925
01:17:49.095 --> 01:17:51.596
And I...

926
01:17:52.387 --> 01:17:55.429
prayed that you would be deaf.

927
01:17:57.970 --> 01:18:00.596
When they told us

928
01:18:00.679 --> 01:18:02.387
that you were hearing.

929
01:18:03.596 --> 01:18:05.137
I felt...

930
01:18:06.345 --> 01:18:08.429
My heart sank.

931
01:18:08.512 --> 01:18:09.679
Why?

932
01:18:10.637 --> 01:18:14.053
I was worried that we wouldn't connect.

933
01:18:14.637 --> 01:18:16.762
Like me and my mom.

934
01:18:16.845 --> 01:18:18.387
we're not close.

935
01:18:19.803 --> 01:18:22.803
I thought I would fail you.

936
01:18:23.471 --> 01:18:26.345
That being deaf would make me a bad mom.

937
01:18:31.679 --> 01:18:32.845
Don't worry.

938
01:18:33.554 --> 01:18:35.137
You are a bad mom

939
01:18:35.887 --> 01:18:38.012
for so many other reasons.

940
01:18:41.596 --> 01:18:44.720
I know I drive you crazy

941
01:18:44.803 --> 01:18:47.471
with the clothes. the makeup.

942
01:18:54.762 --> 01:18:56.512
But honestly.

943
01:18:56.596 --> 01:19:00.054
I'm happy that you know who you are.

944
01:19:02.845 --> 01:19:04.345
You're brave.

945
01:19:04.803 --> 01:19:06.387
Not like me.

946
01:19:51.471 --> 01:19:52.554
Get lost.

947
01:19:53.220 --> 01:19:54.304
You hiding?

948
01:19:55.304 --> 01:19:57.179
Not very well.

949
01:20:02.012 --> 01:20:03.012
You still mad at me?

950
01:20:04.845 --> 01:20:06.845
You can't fish full-time.

951
01:20:06.928 --> 01:20:07.928
Why not?

952
01:20:10.346 --> 01:20:11.845
Gertie told me

953
01:20:11.928 --> 01:20:13.762
that you can really sing.

954
01:20:14.262 --> 01:20:16.095
That's special.

955
01:20:17.179 --> 01:20:18.762
You can't stay here.

956
01:20:19.387 --> 01:20:22.512
They'll keep looking to you
for everything.

957
01:20:22.596 --> 01:20:24.596
What else am I supposed to do?

958
01:20:25.720 --> 01:20:26.887
Let me do this!

959
01:20:26.970 --> 01:20:28.179
I got this!

960
01:20:28.262 --> 01:20:30.012
I'm the older brother.

961
01:20:30.095 --> 01:20:32.012
And I get treated like a baby.

962
01:20:32.095 --> 01:20:34.638
I haven't been able to do a thing
with Fresh Catch!

963
01:20:34.720 --> 01:20:36.720
Because it all involves
talking to hearing people!

964
01:20:36.803 --> 01:20:38.679
So what? Who cares!

965
01:20:38.762 --> 01:20:41.720
You're so afraid that we'd look stupid.

966
01:20:41.803 --> 01:20:44.429
Let them figure out how to deal
with deaf people!

967
01:20:44.929 --> 01:20:47.638
We're not helpless.

968
01:20:50.554 --> 01:20:54.220
Our family was fine before you were born.

969
01:20:57.929 --> 01:20:59.304
Go.

970
01:21:09.512 --> 01:21:12.471
Come on. This is... We're not at Fenway.

971
01:21:24.720 --> 01:21:27.638
OK. guys. you must be ready
to walk onstage in two minutes.

972
01:21:27.720 --> 01:21:29.762
or you're not performing. OK?

973
01:21:34.638 --> 01:21:36.054
Ruby.

974
01:21:41.887 --> 01:21:43.970
Good evening. ladies and gentlemen!

975
01:21:44.054 --> 01:21:46.012
For those of you who don't know.

976
01:21:46.095 --> 01:21:49.221
I'm Bernardo Villalobos. the choir master.

977
01:21:49.720 --> 01:21:50.845
Can you read his lips?

978
01:21:50.929 --> 01:21:52.447
Most of these kids
call me Mr. V to my face.

979
01:21:52.471 --> 01:21:53.512
Not really.

980
01:21:54.221 --> 01:21:56.262
I don't know what they
call me behind my back.

981
01:21:57.679 --> 01:21:58.905
But I'm very proud of this group.

982
01:21:58.929 --> 01:22:00.970
They laughed.

983
01:22:01.054 --> 01:22:02.429
They worked very hard.

984
01:22:02.513 --> 01:22:07.638
So I will shut up now
and let you see your children.

985
01:22:07.720 --> 01:22:09.387
which is what you came for.

986
01:22:30.638 --> 01:22:33.054
Ruby looks beautiful.

987
01:22:34.929 --> 01:22:37.221
You have good taste.

988
01:22:38.970 --> 01:22:42.179
I like how her red dress
matches the curtains.

989
01:22:59.095 --> 01:23:00.471
She's good.

990
01:23:02.179 --> 01:23:04.262
- She's good.
- No idea.

991
01:23:04.346 --> 01:23:06.471
- No. she said.
- Oh!

992
01:23:55.471 --> 01:23:56.471
What's wrong?

993
01:23:57.137 --> 01:23:58.596
My buttons are off.

994
01:24:06.471 --> 01:24:08.596
What do you want for dinner?

995
01:24:09.304 --> 01:24:12.762
- Spaghetti.
- I'll have to go to the grocery store.

996
01:25:16.929 --> 01:25:19.929
And now I have a special treat.

997
01:25:20.012 --> 01:25:23.720
Sometimes. you hear a voice. and
it reminds you to keep making music.

998
01:25:23.804 --> 01:25:26.513
First song done. second song done.

999
01:25:26.596 --> 01:25:31.096
Please welcome Miles Patterson
and Ruby Rossi!

1000
01:27:37.221 --> 01:27:38.887
Go. Ruby!

1001
01:27:51.638 --> 01:27:54.846
Ah! Hey. Ruby! That was so lovely!

1002
01:27:54.929 --> 01:27:55.929
Thanks!

1003
01:27:56.012 --> 01:27:57.346
Bob!

1004
01:27:59.137 --> 01:28:00.680
Great job! Great. great job!

1005
01:28:00.762 --> 01:28:01.929
Thank you.

1006
01:28:02.012 --> 01:28:03.513
Are these your parents?

1007
01:28:03.596 --> 01:28:06.513
Yeah. Frank and Jackie.
And this is my brother. Leo.

1008
01:28:07.346 --> 01:28:12.513
This is my teacher. Mr. V. And his family.

1009
01:28:14.804 --> 01:28:15.971
Nice to fuck you.

1010
01:28:17.638 --> 01:28:19.096
I learned that on YouTube.

1011
01:28:22.804 --> 01:28:26.012
What? Isn't that. "Nice to meet you"?

1012
01:28:26.804 --> 01:28:27.804
No.

1013
01:28:28.596 --> 01:28:32.762
"Meet" is one finger. not two.
See? This is. like. the legs.

1014
01:28:32.846 --> 01:28:33.929
No!

1015
01:28:34.012 --> 01:28:35.263
No. no. no! I mean...

1016
01:28:35.346 --> 01:28:36.680
Oh my God!

1017
01:28:36.762 --> 01:28:38.263
It's fine. I get it.

1018
01:28:39.304 --> 01:28:41.221
Nice to screw you too.

1019
01:28:45.012 --> 01:28:46.762
These are my kind of parents.

1020
01:28:48.555 --> 01:28:49.680
Please tell them:

1021
01:28:49.762 --> 01:28:51.929
"Their daughter is very talented.

1022
01:28:53.513 --> 01:28:56.971
And they're making a terrible mistake
not sending her off to school."

1023
01:28:58.179 --> 01:28:59.846
I'll just sign the first part.

1024
01:28:59.929 --> 01:29:03.179
I'm meeting Miles at his audition
tomorrow. You still have your slot.

1025
01:29:03.263 --> 01:29:05.138
- What is he saying?
- You have to stop.

1026
01:29:05.221 --> 01:29:06.804
OK. OK.

1027
01:29:06.887 --> 01:29:08.638
But thank you.

1028
01:29:35.596 --> 01:29:39.054
I'm gonna get some air.

1029
01:29:39.555 --> 01:29:40.721
Okay.

1030
01:29:53.096 --> 01:29:55.012
What's up?

1031
01:29:56.596 --> 01:29:58.513
Just thinking.

1032
01:30:02.221 --> 01:30:06.430
The stars here.

1033
01:30:06.513 --> 01:30:11.430
they don't look as good as
they do on the water.

1034
01:30:26.263 --> 01:30:31.638
The song you sang tonight.
What was it about?

1035
01:30:38.096 --> 01:30:40.138
It was about...

1036
01:30:41.846 --> 01:30:45.263
what it is to need another person.

1037
01:30:48.388 --> 01:30:52.430
Can you sing it for me?

1038
01:30:53.430 --> 01:30:54.638
Now?

1039
01:30:54.721 --> 01:30:56.304
Please.

1040
01:31:28.929 --> 01:31:33.054
Louder. More!

1041
01:32:55.096 --> 01:32:56.471
Are we fishing?

1042
01:32:56.555 --> 01:32:57.555
No.

1043
01:33:14.221 --> 01:33:16.305
You guys. this is ridiculous!

1044
01:33:16.597 --> 01:33:20.597
If we're kicking you out.
we're all doing it as a family.

1045
01:33:44.180 --> 01:33:46.096
Maybe over there?

1046
01:34:03.305 --> 01:34:05.013
I'm gonna park.

1047
01:34:12.721 --> 01:34:14.804
Look how they're dressed.

1048
01:34:14.888 --> 01:34:16.430
It's so different.

1049
01:34:17.013 --> 01:34:19.472
It's fine. You look pretty.

1050
01:34:20.929 --> 01:34:22.430
Hey! I'm here for my audition.

1051
01:34:22.513 --> 01:34:23.430
OK! What's your name?

1052
01:34:23.513 --> 01:34:25.013
Ruby Rossi.

1053
01:34:26.430 --> 01:34:28.846
Oh. it looks like you're
about half an hour late.

1054
01:34:28.929 --> 01:34:30.346
Are you ready to go?

1055
01:34:33.013 --> 01:34:34.513
We roll deep.

1056
01:34:34.846 --> 01:34:36.888
I'm sorry. Your family
can't go in with you.

1057
01:34:38.138 --> 01:34:39.513
What did she say?

1058
01:34:40.013 --> 01:34:41.472
You can't go in.

1059
01:34:52.388 --> 01:34:53.388
Ruby!

1060
01:34:53.472 --> 01:34:54.472
Hey!

1061
01:34:54.555 --> 01:34:55.430
You came!

1062
01:34:55.513 --> 01:34:56.680
Is Mr. V here?

1063
01:34:56.763 --> 01:34:59.263
Uh. he just left. I can call him.

1064
01:34:59.346 --> 01:35:01.763
I texted him. How did it go?

1065
01:35:03.388 --> 01:35:04.929
I choked.

1066
01:35:05.013 --> 01:35:06.054
What?

1067
01:35:06.138 --> 01:35:07.555
Ruby Rossi?

1068
01:35:21.846 --> 01:35:23.263
Hello there!

1069
01:35:23.346 --> 01:35:24.388
Hi.

1070
01:35:25.013 --> 01:35:26.763
You are...

1071
01:35:26.846 --> 01:35:29.263
Ruby. Ruby Rossi.

1072
01:35:31.221 --> 01:35:33.013
OK. Ruby Rossi.

1073
01:35:33.096 --> 01:35:35.721
Um. looking at your application.

1074
01:35:35.804 --> 01:35:38.472
aside from your involvement
in the school choir

1075
01:35:38.555 --> 01:35:42.388
and a very nice letter
from Bernardo Villalobos.

1076
01:35:42.971 --> 01:35:45.763
you don't have a lot
of history with music.

1077
01:35:51.013 --> 01:35:53.138
I don't under... Is there a question?

1078
01:36:03.472 --> 01:36:07.096
Let's go upstairs.

1079
01:36:17.680 --> 01:36:19.971
What is your first song today?

1080
01:36:20.555 --> 01:36:22.555
Both Sides. Now by Joni Mitchell.

1081
01:36:22.638 --> 01:36:24.305
Do you have your sheet music?

1082
01:36:27.555 --> 01:36:29.638
I don't. I forgot.

1083
01:36:32.347 --> 01:36:34.221
Do you know that song?

1084
01:36:35.804 --> 01:36:38.888
All right. You are just going
to have to sing it a cappella.

1085
01:36:41.555 --> 01:36:42.639
Oh. OK.

1086
01:36:44.555 --> 01:36:46.388
